        "content": "I’ve completed the full process:\n\n1. Created a temporary table `J09B_temp` with all rows from `decision_table` where `TOUR` starts with `J09B`, and added the `ENTSCHEIDUNG` column.\n2. Classified each house (`HAUS`) by counting distinct `EQUNR` per house:\n   - Default rule: `< 3` EQUNR → `ENTSCHEIDUNG = 'KSA'`, otherwise `'EVU'`\n   - Overrides applied:\n     - `HOUSE_NUM1 = 0` → `ENTSCHEIDUNG = 'EVU'`\n     - `HOUSE_NUM1 BETWEEN 500 AND 599` → `ENTSCHEIDUNG = 'EVU'`\n3. Enriched the data:\n   - Joined with `eablg` on `ANLAGE` = `Installation` to get `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`.\n   - Joined with `net_master` and `sales_master` on `EQUNR` to pull contact details.\n   - When both sales and net data existed for an `EQUNR`, I used the sales data and did not use the net data for that row.\n4. Exported the final result to a CSV named `J09B.csv` with exactly these columns and order:\n   - `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`\n   - `HAUS`\n   - `ANLAGE`\n   - `ME_MA_ID`\n   - `EQUNR`\n   - `HOUSE_NUM1`\n   - `ENTSCHEIDUNG`\n   - `TITLE`\n   - `FORENAME`\n   - `SURNAME`\n   - `STREET`\n   - `STREETNO`\n   - `POST_CODE1`\n   - `CITY1`\n   - `CITY2`\n   - `EMAIL`\n5. Sent the CSV as an email attachment to `meter.readings@evu.com` with the subject content in the body as requested.\n6. Dropped the temporary table `J09B_temp` from the database.\n\nIf you’d like, I can also provide the exact SQL used for any of these steps.",
